  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large skillet, heat 2 tbsp of oil over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the lamb and cook until browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the onion and garlic and cook until softened, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add the parsley, rosemary, and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together the egg substitute, heavy cream, and cheddar cheese.",
    "Pour the wet ingredients over the lamb mixture and stir to combine.",
    "Sprinkle the flour over the top and cook for 1-2 minutes.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a greased 9-inch pie dish.",
    "Mix the breadcrumbs with a pinch of salt and sprinkle over the top of the frittata.",
    "Bake for 20-25 minutes or until the top is golden brown and crispy.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool for a few minutes before slicing and serving."
  ],
